    {
      "name": "AnnotatorController",
      "description": "br.com.mechanic.account.controller.annotator.AnnotatorController — POST cria vínculo; PUT .../annotator-link/resume atualiza o resumo; GET .../topic-annotator-links lista vínculos do anotador (conta no path ACTIVE). Query opcionais: topic_id, topic_owner_account_id, topic_status (enum TopicStatusEnum, ex. OPEN, CLOSED; AND com demais filtros). Resposta enriquecida: topic_status, topic_owner_name, resume, timestamps. Não valida dono do tópico ACTIVE nem status do tópico para autorizar a listagem.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Listar vínculos do anotador (GET /api/v1/accounts/{annotatorAccountId}/topic-annotator-links)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/{{annotatorAccountId}}/topic-annotator-links",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "accounts", "{{annotatorAccountId}}", "topic-annotator-links"],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "topic_id",
                  "value": "{{topicId}}",
                  "description": "Opcional. Filtra por id do tópico (snake_case, alinhado ao @RequestParam do controller).",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "topic_owner_account_id",
                  "value": "{{accountId}}",
                  "description": "Opcional. Filtra pela conta dona do tópico. Use a mesma variável que no POST do vínculo (dono = accountId no path de .../topics/...).",
                  "disabled": true
                },
                {
                  "key": "topic_status",
                  "value": "{{topicStatus}}",
                  "description": "Opcional. Valor do enum (ex. OPEN, CLOSED). Tópicos ANNOTATOR sem status na base não casam com valores não-nulos.",
                  "disabled": true
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Path: /api/v1/accounts/{{annotatorAccountId}}/topic-annotator-links — `annotatorAccountId` (coleção) = conta do **anotador** (obrigatório ACTIVE). Query opcionais em snake_case: `topic_id`, `topic_owner_account_id`, `topic_status` (AND entre todos os parâmetros informados). Sem filtros: todos os registros em `topic_annotator_link` com `annotator_account_id` = path.\n\nResposta: JSON array de itens com `id`, `topic_id`, `topic_status` (pode ser null no JSON de resposta), `topic_owner_account_id`, `topic_owner_name`, `annotator_account_id`, `resume`, `created_at`, `last_updated_at`. Ordenação: `created_at` DESC.\n\nDica: rode antes o POST .../annotator-link com os mesmos `accountId` (dono), `topicId` e `annotatorAccountId` da coleção para popular dados."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorAccountId')) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('annotatorAccountId', '2');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200); });",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Corpo é array JSON', function () { pm.expect(body).to.be.an('array'); });",
                  "if (body.length > 0) {",
                  "  const row = body[0];",
                  "  pm.test('Primeiro item: campos snake_case do contrato', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('id');",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('topic_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('topic_status');",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('topic_owner_account_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('topic_owner_name');",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('annotator_account_id');",
                  "    pm.expect(row.annotator_account_id).to.eql(Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorAccountId')));",
                  "    pm.expect(row).to.have.property('created_at');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Vincular anotador ao topico (POST .../topics/{topicId}/annotator-link)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/{{accountId}}/topics/{{topicId}}/annotator-link",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "accounts",
                "{{accountId}}",
                "topics",
                "{{topicId}}",
                "annotator-link"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"annotator_account_id\": {{annotatorAccountId}}\n}"
            },
            "description": "Corpo: somente annotator_account_id (snake_case). Resumo: use PUT .../annotator-link/resume.\n\nRegras: topico da conta; dono e anotador ACTIVE; anotador perfil ANNOTATOR; se profile_type do topico nao for ANNOTATOR, annotator_account_id != dono; par (topicId, annotator) unico.\n\nResposta 201: resume omitido ate o PUT; created_at; last_updated_at null no create."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.environment.get('accountId')) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('accountId', 1);",
                  "}",
                  "if (!pm.environment.get('topicId')) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('topicId', 1);",
                  "}",
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorAccountId')) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('annotatorAccountId', '2');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(201); });",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Corpo do link', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.id).to.be.a('number');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.topic_id).to.eql(Number(pm.environment.get('topicId')));",
                  "  pm.expect(json.topic_owner_account_id).to.eql(Number(pm.environment.get('accountId')));",
                  "  pm.expect(json.annotator_account_id).to.eql(Number(pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorAccountId')));",
                  "  pm.expect(json.created_at).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.environment.set('topicAnnotatorLinkId', json.id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Atualizar resumo do vínculo (PUT .../annotator-link/resume)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/{{accountId}}/topics/{{topicId}}/annotator-link/resume",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "v1",
                "accounts",
                "{{accountId}}",
                "topics",
                "{{topicId}}",
                "annotator-link",
                "resume"
              ]
            },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"annotator_account_id\": {{annotatorAccountId}},\n  \"resume\": \"{{annotatorLinkResumeUpdate}}\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Obrigatório: annotator_account_id e resume (texto grande). Pré-requisito: POST .../annotator-link com o mesmo par (topicId, annotator). Dono do tópico ACTIVE; tópico OPEN (se tiver workflow); anotador ACTIVE. Resposta 200 TopicAnnotatorLinkResponse com last_updated_at e resume."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorLinkResumeUpdate')) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('annotatorLinkResumeUpdate', 'Resumo atualizado via PUT resume.');",
                  "}",
                  "if (!pm.environment.get('accountId')) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('accountId', 1);",
                  "}",
                  "if (!pm.environment.get('topicId')) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set('topicId', 1);",
                  "}",
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorAccountId')) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('annotatorAccountId', '2');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200); });",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('resume e last_updated_at', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.resume).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('annotatorLinkResumeUpdate'));",
                  "  pm.expect(json.last_updated_at).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "TopicController",
      "description": "Conta ACTIVE obrigatoria em GET/POST/PUT/PATCH de topicos.\n\nListagem GET .../topics: page, size; filtros opcionais status e profile_type (snake_case), sozinhos ou em AND. Nao combine status com profile_type=ANNOTATOR (400).\n\nAuditoria topic_history (sem endpoint REST): ao criar topico com status persistido (ex. OPEN), grava-se OPEN; ao fechar (PATCH .../close), grava-se CLOSED com created_at. ANNOTATOR sem status nao gera linha na criacao.\n\nFechar: PATCH .../topics/{topicId}/close — apenas se status atual for OPEN.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Listar topicos (GET /api/v1/accounts/{accountId}/topics)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/{{accountId}}/topics?page=0&size=20",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "accounts", "{{accountId}}", "topics"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "status", "value": "{{topicStatus}}", "description": "Opcional (ex. OPEN). Adicione na URL se precisar.", "disabled": true },
                { "key": "profile_type", "value": "{{topicProfileType}}", "description": "Opcional (ex. SPEAKER). Adicione na URL; combine com status se quiser AND.", "disabled": true }
              ]
            },
            "description": "TopicPageResponse paginado. Ative status e/ou profile_type para filtrar (AND). Nao use status junto com profile_type=ANNOTATOR. Sem filtros: todos os topicos da conta."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Obter topico por id (GET /api/v1/accounts/{accountId}/topics/{topicId})",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/{{accountId}}/topics/{{topicId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "accounts", "{{accountId}}", "topics", "{{topicId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Somente se o topico pertencer ao accountId. Caso contrario 400 (mesma mensagem que topico inexistente)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Fechar topico OPEN → CLOSED (PATCH /api/v1/accounts/{accountId}/topics/{topicId}/close)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/accounts/{{accountId}}/topics/{{topicId}}/close",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "accounts", "{{accountId}}", "topics", "{{topicId}}", "close"]
            },
